magpie.data.utilities.generators

Class CompositionRangeEntryGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • magpie.data.utilities.generators.BaseEntryGenerator
      • magpie.data.utilities.generators.CompositionRangeEntryGenerator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<BaseEntry>, Options

    public class CompositionRangeEntryGenerator
extends BaseEntryGenerator
    Create compositions in a rectangular, user-specified grid. User should specify the base element along with the minimum, maximum, and step size for each element to be added. It is also possible to define the minimum and maximum amount of a base element

    Example: Al with 0-10at% Ni and 0-10at% Zr in step sizes of 0.2at%

    Usage: <base> [-min <min base fraction>] [-max <max base fraction>] -alloy <alloy elem> <alloy min> <alloy max> <alloy step> [<...>]
    base: Symbol of base element
    min base fraction: Optional: Minimum fraction of base element
    max base fraction: Optional: Maximum fraction of base element
    alloy elem: Symbol of alloying element
    alloy elem: Minimum fraction of alloying element
    alloy elem: Maximum fraction of alloying element
    alloy elem: Step size of alloying element User can supply any number of alloying elements
